1
00:00:20,208 --> 00:00:22,166
Greetings, Valkenhayn.

2
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:24,291
[VALKENHAYN] A pleasure
to have you home again.

3
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:26,541
Your tea is at the ready.

4
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:29,041
Very well, then.

5
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:35,958
Something troubles
you, milady.

6
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:39,083
The blindness
of spectators.

7
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:41,583
You speak of
Takamagahara?

8
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:45,291
I do. Terumi's running amok.

9
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:50,208
[VALKENHAYN] If that trickster
has been let off of his leash,

10
00:00:50,291 --> 00:00:53,541
why, there's no telling
the trouble he'll stir up.

11
00:00:53,625 --> 00:00:55,500
[RACHEL] It vexes me.

12
00:00:55,583 --> 00:00:57,750
Forgive my impertinence,
Madam Rachel,

13
00:00:57,833 --> 00:01:00,666
but does it really?

14
00:01:00,750 --> 00:01:02,708
Forgiven. Explain.

15
00:01:02,791 --> 00:01:05,041
I could have sworn
there was a smile

16
00:01:05,125 --> 00:01:07,333
tugging at your lips.

17
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:09,833
It seems your
eyes deceive you.

18
00:01:09,916 --> 00:01:11,541
I did no such thing.

19
00:01:11,625 --> 00:01:14,375
The perils
of age, milady.

20
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:21,458
[RACHEL] Drunk on
time's heady brew,

21
00:01:21,541 --> 00:01:23,916
the world lay on
the edge of slumber.

22
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
It was poised to
slip into a dream

23
00:01:26,083 --> 00:01:28,125
from which there is no waking.

24
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:31,875
But now, there comes a
knock at the chamber door.

25
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:35,250
Then time no longer
repeats as it did prior.

26
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:38,666
And the event we anticipated
is already at hand.

27
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:39,958
Correct?

28
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:41,541
Indeed.

29
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:47,541
Well, then. What is
your course of action?

30
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:51,458
I am but a spectator.
While others act,

31
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:54,666
I merely watch their
deeds for eternity.

32
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:56,666
It is a thankless task.

33
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:59,583
So I, Valkenhayn, shall
dedicate whatever's left

34
00:01:59,666 --> 00:02:01,833
of my meager existence
to bringing you

35
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:04,333
[VALKENHAYN]
comfort 'midst your vigil.

36
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:46,458
[KOKONOE] This is Kokonoe.
Hey, talk to me, Tager.

37
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:50,500
[TAGER] Roger that, Kokonoe.
I'm currently airborne,

38
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:54,000
